To us 6 months is a very short time in a business cycle. Clearly to people like Dunderhead Johnston we must be JP Morgan Chase. We are, as described by both parties, the fabric of America with less than 30 employees. Smart people realize that the more you pound small businesses down, the more you regulate them, the less chance that they will grow or survive.
